<TITLE> Khaleda pays respects to Zia in low-key death anniversary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.com)BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia Wednesday paused in silence to commemorate the late president Ziaur Rahman. The former prime minister offered flowers at Zia's grave in Sher-e-Bangla Nagar at 11am in a low-key 26th death anniversary of the former president. BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, former finance and planning minister M Saifur Rahman, former information minister M Shamsul Islam and others accompanied Khaleda. Earlier, president Iajuddin Ahmed, chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed and speaker Jamiruddin Sircar placed wreaths to pay respects to Zia. The president and the chief adviser stood in solemn silence for a few minutes after placing wreaths separately, when military bugles played the last post. In response to BNP's request, the caretaker government Monday allowed 150 people to assemble at Zia's grave. On March 17, the chief adviser paid respects and offered fateha at the mazar of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman in Tungipara to mark his birth anniversary. bdnews24.
